parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking or deterioration of the fuel rail can cause a fuel leak into the engine compartment, leading to a fire hazard.
Fuel line leaks can cause a fuel leak into the engine compartment, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: fuel spraying from the fuel line

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair the fuel rail or fuel line can lead to continued fuel leaks and fire hazards.
symptoms: vehicle catching on fire after recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel injector can cause poor gas mileage and potentially lead to fuel leaks.

The failure of the power window motor can cause inconvenience and discomfort for the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may lead to safety issues if the window becomes stuck in a position that obstructs the driver's view.
symptoms: The power window does not move when the button is pressed
the power window moves slowly or erratically
the power window gets stuck in a position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior rear view mirror can cause a distraction or obstruction for the driver, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The interior rear view mirror falls off the windshield
the interior rear view mirror becomes loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause discomfort and inconvenience for the driver and passengers, particularly in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The blower motor does not turn on
the blower motor produces a loud noise
the blower motor does not produce adequate airflow.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag sensors can cause unintended air bag deployment, potentially leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: the air bag warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or death to occupants. Additionally, unintended airbag deployment can cause distractions, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: airbags fail to deploy in a crash
